1
00:00:55,041 --> 00:00:59,444
When people finish their day
and hurry home,

2
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:01,791
my day starts.

3
00:01:19,166 --> 00:01:23,533
My diner is open from midnight
to 7:00 in the morning.

4
00:01:24,006 --> 00:01:27,381
They call it "Midnight Diner."

5
00:01:32,808 --> 00:01:34,766
Do I even have customers?

6
00:01:34,766 --> 00:01:36,638
More than you would expect.

7
00:01:39,155 --> 00:01:41,120
MIDNIGHT DINER: TOKYO STORIES

8
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:46,761
CURRY RAMEN

9
00:01:48,538 --> 00:01:50,121
-One more.
-Thanks.

10
00:01:59,294 --> 00:02:00,172
Welcome.

11
00:02:00,544 --> 00:02:03,736
Um... Do you have curry ramen?

12
00:02:04,782 --> 00:02:05,990
Curry ramen?

13
00:02:07,773 --> 00:02:10,065
So, ramen on top of curry?

14
00:02:11,153 --> 00:02:14,028
Actually, ramen with curry on top.

15
00:02:15,544 --> 00:02:16,461
Sure.

16
00:02:33,830 --> 00:02:37,513
As I happened to have some
salt-flavored instant ramen,

17
00:02:37,513 --> 00:02:39,530
I made a thin broth,

18
00:02:39,530 --> 00:02:42,613
and poured some of my curry on top.

19
00:02:56,381 --> 00:02:57,416
How is it?

20
00:02:57,688 --> 00:02:59,669
Delicious. Thank you.

21
00:03:00,396 --> 00:03:03,044
His name is Kabayama.

22
00:03:03,405 --> 00:03:08,908
He came because he heard
I would make whatever customers wanted.

23
00:03:09,397 --> 00:03:10,981
Curry and ramen...

24
00:03:11,551 --> 00:03:14,218
What a luxury to have the two together!

25
00:03:15,515 --> 00:03:17,989
Can I have half a bowl of rice as well?

26
00:03:18,583 --> 00:03:19,458
Sure.

27
00:03:31,285 --> 00:03:33,477
What a great combination!

28
00:03:33,477 --> 00:03:35,477
Ramen and rice.

29
00:03:38,325 --> 00:03:41,575
Consuming too many carbs
causes weight gain.

30
00:03:41,575 --> 00:03:43,231
Especially at night.

31
00:03:43,641 --> 00:03:45,058
I know.

32
00:03:45,058 --> 00:03:47,050
It's hard to explain,

33
00:03:47,464 --> 00:03:52,196
but the rebelliousness of eating ramen
and rice at night makes it taste better.

34
00:03:52,486 --> 00:03:55,076
Master, ramen and a half bowl
of fried rice, please!

35
00:03:57,190 --> 00:04:00,467
Definitely not!
You'll end up in the hospital again.

36
00:04:00,991 --> 00:04:02,950
Not even a little?

37
00:04:04,408 --> 00:04:06,841
Show some self-control.

38
00:04:07,414 --> 00:04:09,448
Your diabetes is finally
under control, right?

39
00:04:09,988 --> 00:04:11,988
Thanks to your wife being a nurse.

40
00:04:13,908 --> 00:04:15,721
Cancel that order, please.

41
00:04:16,450 --> 00:04:17,194
Sure.

42
00:04:18,075 --> 00:04:19,116
I'm sorry.

43
00:04:49,296 --> 00:04:50,338
Excuse me...

44
00:04:51,990 --> 00:04:53,990
Are you Mr. Shuichi Tachibana?

45
00:04:56,359 --> 00:04:57,317
Who are you?

46
00:04:58,467 --> 00:04:59,300
Kabayama.

47
00:04:59,866 --> 00:05:00,662
Kabayama?

48
00:05:01,036 --> 00:05:03,202
I guess you don't remember me.

49
00:05:05,046 --> 00:05:06,088
Kabayama?

50
00:05:09,570 --> 00:05:12,154
-From Higashi Junior High?
-That's right.

51
00:05:14,045 --> 00:05:15,045
Dorkayama...

52
00:05:16,828 --> 00:05:18,245
Tsuyoshi Dorkayama!

53
00:05:19,411 --> 00:05:21,952
We were in the same class
in seventh grade, right?

54
00:05:22,866 --> 00:05:25,544
-How are you?
-Yeah.

55
00:05:26,924 --> 00:05:29,211
Master, two of the usual.

56
00:05:29,643 --> 00:05:30,518
Sure.

57
00:05:31,492 --> 00:05:35,420
What a coincidence,
bumping into an old classmate like that.

58
00:05:36,325 --> 00:05:37,533
It sure is.

59
00:05:38,736 --> 00:05:41,100
I'm amazed you recognized me,

60
00:05:41,100 --> 00:05:43,153
even though I haven't seen you
since graduation.

61
00:05:43,153 --> 00:05:45,730
Of course I remember you.

62
00:05:45,730 --> 00:05:49,458
He was the school council president
and the soccer captain.

63
00:05:49,458 --> 00:05:51,650
The girls always flocked around him.

64
00:05:52,398 --> 00:05:55,773
So you were like Yujiro Ishihara?

65
00:05:56,491 --> 00:05:59,508
What era are you living in?
Don't exaggerate.

66
00:06:00,528 --> 00:06:05,234
He was my hero.
No, not just mine, everybody's.

67
00:06:05,234 --> 00:06:06,483
Give it a rest.

68
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:08,798
Everyone's listening.

69
00:06:08,798 --> 00:06:11,164
And so what happened after that?

70
00:06:11,549 --> 00:06:13,395
He went on to a private school,

71
00:06:13,395 --> 00:06:15,520
and his team was one of
the best in the prefecture.

72
00:06:16,863 --> 00:06:18,327
You know a lot about me.

73
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:21,160
When I heard you got into
Hitotsubashi University,

74
00:06:21,160 --> 00:06:23,445
I had a drink in celebration.

75
00:06:23,838 --> 00:06:26,254
What? Come on, man, that's weird!

76
00:06:27,422 --> 00:06:28,839
What are you doing now?

77
00:06:29,938 --> 00:06:30,896
Now?

78
00:06:32,181 --> 00:06:33,223
Now...

79
00:06:33,977 --> 00:06:36,534
I'm biding my time.

80
00:06:36,926 --> 00:06:38,801
Waiting for the moment to strike.

81
00:06:41,058 --> 00:06:43,641
Here you are, curry ramens.

82
00:06:46,268 --> 00:06:48,022
This is so nostalgic!

83
00:06:48,398 --> 00:06:50,848
This was my favorite during junior high!

84
00:06:50,848 --> 00:06:52,598
-You, too, Kabayama?
-Yep.

85
00:06:54,229 --> 00:06:55,521
Thanks for the food.

86
00:06:59,228 --> 00:07:00,879
Wow, this is great!

87
00:07:00,879 --> 00:07:04,326
I prepared this curry last night.

88
00:07:04,326 --> 00:07:06,346
That's the way to do it.

89
00:07:12,524 --> 00:07:14,774
Why did I used to eat such a thing?

90
00:07:18,157 --> 00:07:21,823
Kabayama, can you lend me some money?

91
00:07:23,980 --> 00:07:25,147
Sure.

92
00:07:28,636 --> 00:07:31,386
I only have 20,000 on me.

93
00:07:31,386 --> 00:07:35,256
That's fine. I'll pay you back double
after I win on the horses.

94
00:07:43,606 --> 00:07:45,256
Tachibana is really amazing.

95
00:07:45,256 --> 00:07:48,881
The last time he paid me back
triple what I lent him.

96
00:07:49,539 --> 00:07:54,024
Shouldn't you be careful about
mixing money and friendship?

97
00:07:54,706 --> 00:07:58,039
They say, "When the money runs out,
so does the friendship."

98
00:08:04,025 --> 00:08:05,038
Yo!

99
00:08:05,951 --> 00:08:07,451
Tachibana!

100
00:08:07,866 --> 00:08:08,926
Welcome.

101
00:08:09,197 --> 00:08:10,266
Two curry ramens.

102
00:08:10,543 --> 00:08:11,709
Sure.

103
00:08:13,758 --> 00:08:15,550
Hinano said she wanted to try it.

104
00:08:24,069 --> 00:08:25,027
How is it?

105
00:08:27,408 --> 00:08:29,824
It might be better with melted cheese.

106
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:33,480
Master, can we have
some cheese for the curry?

107
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:34,414
Sure.

108
00:08:49,059 --> 00:08:52,517
Women always want to add cheese
to everything, don't they?

109
00:08:53,824 --> 00:08:55,695
Curry plus ramen plus...

110
00:08:56,304 --> 00:08:57,669
cheese?

111
00:09:00,167 --> 00:09:02,626
Hinano, give him a business card.

112
00:09:08,433 --> 00:09:09,751
Nice to meet you.

113
00:09:09,751 --> 00:09:11,418
Go visit her some time.

114
00:09:12,395 --> 00:09:14,862
-My name is Kabayama.
-Good to see you.

115
00:09:14,862 --> 00:09:15,675
Kaba-chan!

116
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:18,308
-Kaba-chan?
-Kaba-chan.

117
00:09:40,358 --> 00:09:41,358
Thanks.

118
00:09:43,744 --> 00:09:46,745
Soon, Kabayama and Tachibana

119
00:09:47,243 --> 00:09:50,576
became good friends again,
just like in their school days.

120
00:09:56,599 --> 00:09:57,558
Here.

121
00:09:59,266 --> 00:10:00,183
Thanks.

122
00:10:03,141 --> 00:10:04,515
How did it go yesterday?

123
00:10:05,475 --> 00:10:06,201
What?

124
00:10:06,468 --> 00:10:09,088
Your part-time job interview
at the convenience store.

125
00:10:11,006 --> 00:10:11,839
I didn't go.

126
00:10:12,376 --> 00:10:13,209
Why?

127
00:10:17,749 --> 00:10:20,124
That kind of work isn't for me, you know?

128
00:10:21,477 --> 00:10:24,287
So what is? If this job's
not good enough for you,

129
00:10:24,657 --> 00:10:25,976
then what is?

130
00:10:53,604 --> 00:10:55,741
Kaba-chan, you came!

131
00:10:55,741 --> 00:10:56,995
I'm so happy.

132
00:10:56,995 --> 00:10:58,828
'Cause I promised Tachibana I would.

133
00:10:59,635 --> 00:11:00,377
Please have a seat.

134
00:11:03,811 --> 00:11:07,116
And then the branch manager
at the Kameido store quit,

135
00:11:07,116 --> 00:11:09,296
and my boss recommended me for the job.

136
00:11:09,936 --> 00:11:11,144
Amazing!

137
00:11:11,144 --> 00:11:12,591
You'll be promoted to the manager.

138
00:11:17,109 --> 00:11:20,402
Kaba-chan, why do you look up to Shu-chan?

139
00:11:25,683 --> 00:11:29,194
You have a steady job.
You're doing much better than him.

140
00:11:35,853 --> 00:11:37,312
It bothers me...

141
00:11:37,887 --> 00:11:39,995
the way you cling to him like that.

142
00:11:40,403 --> 00:11:41,694
It reminds me of me.

143
00:11:44,846 --> 00:11:45,680
Sorry.

144
00:11:50,534 --> 00:11:51,784
I guess...

145
00:11:53,510 --> 00:11:54,760
we both want to believe.

146
00:12:04,805 --> 00:12:07,947
I'm finally starting to win, so please,
just one more hour...

147
00:12:08,129 --> 00:12:09,820
Don't make a scene.

148
00:12:10,308 --> 00:12:11,933
I'm begging you, please!

149
00:12:13,641 --> 00:12:15,308
-Please...
-Come on.

150
00:12:20,058 --> 00:12:20,985
You've got...

151
00:12:21,452 --> 00:12:22,702
three kidneys, right?

152
00:12:24,492 --> 00:12:25,867
I've got two.

153
00:12:26,520 --> 00:12:27,540
We'll take one of them.

154
00:12:27,876 --> 00:12:28,792
Calm down.

155
00:12:29,612 --> 00:12:31,987
You have a wallet, right?
How much do you have?

156
00:12:36,851 --> 00:12:38,809
Let's go get you another loan.

157
00:12:39,749 --> 00:12:40,582
Get up.

158
00:12:41,254 --> 00:12:42,171
Get up.

159
00:12:43,344 --> 00:12:44,552
Wait a minute!

160
00:12:45,348 --> 00:12:46,461
Please, wait.

161
00:12:46,861 --> 00:12:48,944
Take this for now.

162
00:12:50,180 --> 00:12:52,237
-What are you...
-It's fine.

163
00:12:52,237 --> 00:12:54,487
You can pay it back little by little.

164
00:12:55,538 --> 00:12:57,288
Okay, then. If you insist.

165
00:12:58,214 --> 00:12:59,988
That's all for today, kid.

166
00:12:59,988 --> 00:13:01,863
Friendship sure is beautiful!

167
00:13:11,024 --> 00:13:12,024
I...

168
00:13:15,079 --> 00:13:17,912
don't really remember you.

169
00:13:18,541 --> 00:13:20,624
I don't even have my yearbook anymore.

170
00:13:49,309 --> 00:13:50,393
Are you open?

171
00:13:59,189 --> 00:14:01,148
That money is nothing...

172
00:14:03,084 --> 00:14:05,950
I don't need him. If I really wanted to...

173
00:14:06,425 --> 00:14:08,508
I could pay it back in a heartbeat!

174
00:14:11,841 --> 00:14:15,300
You think I'm lying, don't you?

175
00:14:16,341 --> 00:14:19,133
I will do it! I can do it!

176
00:14:19,925 --> 00:14:22,883
People believe in me,
and I've never let them down!

177
00:14:25,701 --> 00:14:26,951
Master, one more.

178
00:14:27,866 --> 00:14:28,866
Sorry.

179
00:14:29,433 --> 00:14:32,433
There's a limit of
three bottles per person.

180
00:14:38,846 --> 00:14:41,572
I'll call Dorkayama and go somewhere else.

181
00:14:41,814 --> 00:14:42,981
Kabayama...

182
00:14:43,927 --> 00:14:45,672
You're just using him.

183
00:14:47,842 --> 00:14:50,435
Because he wants me to use him.

184
00:14:52,456 --> 00:14:53,956
You're the type of guy...

185
00:14:55,407 --> 00:14:57,866
who has no confidence, only pride.

186
00:15:01,775 --> 00:15:04,025
You don't know anything about me.

187
00:15:07,763 --> 00:15:09,304
It's not easy, is it?

188
00:15:10,442 --> 00:15:12,025
Admitting your weaknesses.

189
00:15:13,454 --> 00:15:14,288
But...

190
00:15:16,206 --> 00:15:18,164
no matter how long you fake it,

191
00:15:18,164 --> 00:15:19,765
nothing will change.

192
00:15:20,860 --> 00:15:22,401
It's okay to stumble.

193
00:15:23,989 --> 00:15:26,476
As long as you act with honesty...

194
00:15:27,525 --> 00:15:30,275
you'll someday realize your true self.

195
00:15:31,612 --> 00:15:32,654
You know?

196
00:15:48,064 --> 00:15:52,980
After that night,
Tachibana completely disappeared.

197
00:16:19,362 --> 00:16:20,904
They're here again.

198
00:16:22,098 --> 00:16:23,015
Welcome.

199
00:16:23,015 --> 00:16:24,629
Shochu with lemon juice, please.

200
00:16:24,629 --> 00:16:25,463
Sure.

201
00:16:26,258 --> 00:16:27,978
They're here everyday.

202
00:16:28,469 --> 00:16:31,012
Even though he's been gone for two months,

203
00:16:31,482 --> 00:16:32,899
they're still waiting.

204
00:16:35,286 --> 00:16:37,559
They believe in him, right?

205
00:16:38,652 --> 00:16:40,361
It's rare. I think it's beautiful.

206
00:16:43,967 --> 00:16:44,801
Hey...

207
00:16:46,666 --> 00:16:48,041
Let's give it up.

208
00:16:49,458 --> 00:16:52,375
Shu-chan probably found another woman
and lives with her.

209
00:16:58,171 --> 00:17:00,462
Aren't you angry about what he's done?

210
00:17:05,962 --> 00:17:07,296
I'm going home.

211
00:17:10,583 --> 00:17:11,791
You're here.

212
00:17:19,023 --> 00:17:19,940
Here...

213
00:17:21,489 --> 00:17:22,698
I'm paying you back.

214
00:17:25,246 --> 00:17:26,580
I'm sorry it's late.

215
00:17:27,833 --> 00:17:29,000
How did you get that?

216
00:17:32,125 --> 00:17:34,250
I found a job where I could live onsite.

217
00:17:36,621 --> 00:17:38,151
I was working!

218
00:17:42,771 --> 00:17:44,021
Here you go.

219
00:17:44,543 --> 00:17:45,981
-Welcome.
-Hello.

220
00:17:46,303 --> 00:17:48,288
-Master, beer, please.
-Sure.

221
00:17:48,288 --> 00:17:49,330
And...

222
00:17:50,851 --> 00:17:52,560
three curry ramens.

223
00:17:53,779 --> 00:17:54,654
Sure.

224
00:17:56,516 --> 00:17:57,391
Sit.

225
00:18:00,590 --> 00:18:04,715
I also worked at night as a
security guard when I had the energy.

226
00:18:09,328 --> 00:18:12,370
Hey, don't get so emotional!

227
00:18:13,979 --> 00:18:16,062
Everyone is listening!

228
00:18:17,495 --> 00:18:18,329
Okay?

229
00:18:31,419 --> 00:18:32,336
I...

230
00:18:33,405 --> 00:18:35,863
did nothing but work, day and night,

231
00:18:36,561 --> 00:18:37,894
and I finally understood.

232
00:18:39,274 --> 00:18:43,357
I've lived my life thinking
I need to fulfill everyone's expectations.

233
00:18:44,179 --> 00:18:45,470
I overextended myself.

234
00:18:47,929 --> 00:18:50,012
But I'm not a very mature person.

235
00:18:52,523 --> 00:18:54,851
You know me better than anyone, right?

236
00:18:58,417 --> 00:18:59,334
So...

237
00:19:01,151 --> 00:19:02,193
Kabayama.

238
00:19:03,064 --> 00:19:03,939
Please...

239
00:19:05,032 --> 00:19:07,115
stop looking up to me.

240
00:19:08,056 --> 00:19:11,515
See me as the idiot I really am.

241
00:19:12,660 --> 00:19:13,576
Okay?

242
00:19:22,842 --> 00:19:24,050
Tachibana...

243
00:19:25,964 --> 00:19:27,005
I'm...

244
00:19:27,573 --> 00:19:28,844
not Kabayama.

245
00:19:31,591 --> 00:19:34,424
I mean, my family name is Kabayama, but...

246
00:19:35,704 --> 00:19:36,704
I'm the brother.

247
00:19:37,604 --> 00:19:41,151
I'm Takeharu,
the younger brother of your classmate.

248
00:19:42,503 --> 00:19:44,471
Younger brother? What?

249
00:19:44,471 --> 00:19:45,971
Of course, you don't remember.

250
00:19:47,480 --> 00:19:49,573
What happened to him, then?

251
00:19:51,836 --> 00:19:53,128
My elder brother...

252
00:19:54,303 --> 00:19:55,469
died.

253
00:19:56,611 --> 00:19:57,777
Six years ago.

254
00:20:03,607 --> 00:20:05,566
On his way to a school reunion,

255
00:20:06,319 --> 00:20:07,652
he was hit by a car.

256
00:20:09,339 --> 00:20:10,255
I...

257
00:20:11,493 --> 00:20:13,868
hated my brother for being your lackey.

258
00:20:15,111 --> 00:20:16,277
I made fun of him.

259
00:20:18,258 --> 00:20:19,299
And then...

260
00:20:21,005 --> 00:20:22,089
he died.

261
00:20:25,074 --> 00:20:27,365
I hated myself for looking down on him,

262
00:20:28,487 --> 00:20:30,862
so I had been trying
not to think about him.

263
00:20:33,369 --> 00:20:35,496
Why did you pretend to be him?

264
00:20:36,187 --> 00:20:37,185
Well...

265
00:20:37,849 --> 00:20:40,911
That was Tachibana's misunderstanding.

266
00:20:44,505 --> 00:20:45,714
But, I thought...

267
00:20:47,379 --> 00:20:48,962
if I pretended to be my brother

268
00:20:49,501 --> 00:20:51,292
and spent time with Tachibana...

269
00:20:52,979 --> 00:20:54,020
maybe...

270
00:20:55,179 --> 00:20:57,137
I could understand my brother a little.

271
00:21:02,526 --> 00:21:03,693
Mr. Tachibana...

272
00:21:05,101 --> 00:21:06,310
Hinano...

273
00:21:09,403 --> 00:21:10,695
I'm sorry...

274
00:21:11,738 --> 00:21:12,911
for lying.

275
00:21:14,805 --> 00:21:15,680
No...

276
00:21:18,541 --> 00:21:19,624
On the day he died...

277
00:21:21,054 --> 00:21:25,345
I said to him, "Don't go to
the school reunion just to see Tachibana.

278
00:21:27,217 --> 00:21:28,467
You're grown up now,

279
00:21:29,193 --> 00:21:31,675
but you still rely on him for everything."

280
00:21:34,146 --> 00:21:35,146
And he said...

281
00:21:36,981 --> 00:21:38,231
"You don't see it,

282
00:21:39,179 --> 00:21:41,304
but Tachibana is a good guy."

283
00:21:42,431 --> 00:21:43,598
And he smiled.

284
00:21:52,063 --> 00:21:53,730
I gave you that money...

285
00:21:55,109 --> 00:21:57,982
because that's what my brother
would have done.

286
00:22:06,031 --> 00:22:08,822
My brother wasn't wrong.

287
00:22:12,833 --> 00:22:15,015
Right, Hinano?

288
00:22:24,409 --> 00:22:25,349
Here you go.

289
00:22:30,032 --> 00:22:31,073
I remember!

290
00:22:33,157 --> 00:22:35,490
I first tried this at your house.

291
00:22:36,026 --> 00:22:37,484
He made it for me.

292
00:22:45,056 --> 00:22:46,014
Takeharu.

293
00:22:48,386 --> 00:22:49,469
Will you take me...

294
00:22:50,208 --> 00:22:51,916
to visit your brother's grave?

295
00:22:53,358 --> 00:22:54,775
Can I go, too?

296
00:22:55,711 --> 00:22:58,419
I think my brother would like that.

297
00:23:03,316 --> 00:23:04,369
Thanks for the food.

298
00:23:04,565 --> 00:23:05,240
Thanks for the food.

299
00:23:05,325 --> 00:23:06,491
Thanks for the food.

300
00:23:16,190 --> 00:23:19,107
Now I want some curry ramen, too.

301
00:23:19,234 --> 00:23:20,068
Right?

302
00:23:20,682 --> 00:23:23,266
Master, three curry ramens, please.

303
00:23:27,338 --> 00:23:28,713
Actually, four.

304
00:23:29,652 --> 00:23:30,485
Can I have one?

305
00:23:31,047 --> 00:23:33,297
It's just for today.

306
00:23:34,792 --> 00:23:37,417
Fill mine to the top!

307
00:23:37,417 --> 00:23:38,500
Sure.

308
00:23:43,938 --> 00:23:45,063
Here you go.

309
00:23:46,135 --> 00:23:47,135
And yours.

310
00:24:00,733 --> 00:24:04,775
Using less broth balances out
the noodles and curry.

311
00:24:04,775 --> 00:24:05,775
Here you are.

312
00:24:07,148 --> 00:24:09,231
I also recommend shredded cheese with it.

313
00:24:22,189 --> 00:24:23,138
With that...

314
00:24:23,527 --> 00:24:24,944
-Good night!
-Good night!

